As N gets larger, SEM decreases and confidence intervals become more narrow. In short, estimates become more and more accurate the larger the sample. 

As simulations run, the beta estimates become more and more accurate. The results show that the width of the confidence intervals begins to narrow, and the betas become more accurate to the "true" slope from the data gathering equation of 3. By using the command " bysort n_val: sum b " we see that the beta at n=10 is 2.999827, but when n=10000 beta is  3.000289.

